review_content:
A - pours very, very &nbsp;dark cloudy mahogany with high lasting tan head.&nbsp;

S - very subtle aromas. Hard to get a bead on. &nbsp;Hints of earthy yeasts. Cola and dark chocolates. Floral notes as well. Hints of cola, licorice and chocolate.&nbsp;

M - creamy medium bodied beer.

T - Earthy Belgian yeasts with dark chocolate on the nose. Toasted malts, subtle chocolate and smoky earthiness on the nose. Iingering dryish. Hints of licorice and cola throughout.&nbsp;

O - very good dark saison. Subtle thin aroma and weaker taste &nbsp;on the nose. Otherwise very good&nbsp;

7-
